description:
Roles & Responsibilities
Our client, a well-known MNC with a strong international presence in the e-commerce industry, is looking for their first hire in the Legal team.

Role:
• Review and update product terms and policies to ensure compliance with local laws, policies, and requirements in Singapore;
• Monitor and advise on legal and regulatory developments that impact the company’s operations in Singapore and globally;
• Represent the group’s regional headquarter as in-house legal counsel in dealing with regulatory audits, litigations, and investigations, with the support from HQ legal teams;
• Supervise and manage external legal counsel when needed.
• Draft and review contracts, agreements and provide comments and advices;
• Assist in negotiation of contracts for the business;
• Provide counseling and support new initiatives and projects of in Singapore and the region;

Requirements:
• An LLB and bar admission in Singapore is required.
• At least five years PQE with exposure to international legal matters either at a reputable law firm or in an MNC;
• Experience of multi-jurisdictional data privacy practice is required;
• Knowledge in Business Chinese is essential to communicate with stakeholders


If you are interested in this role, please click on Apply Now.
Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted, thank you.

JAC Recruitment Pte. Ltd.
EA Licence Number: 90C3026
Personnel Registration Number: R22105483
Lin Kai Wei

Roles & Responsibilities
Our client is an established public healthcare supply chain agency. Their skilled supply chain professionals shall leverage on data analytics, forge strategic partnerships, and tap emerging technologies and other innovative solutions to improve and future-proof Singapore’s healthcare supply chain landscape and to better meet the needs of the public healthcare.
They are looking for an individual to join them in their growing team, here is your chance to be part of an exciting team geared towards both company and personal success.
SENIOR / PRINCIPAL LEGAL COUNSEL
As a Principal / Senior Legal Counsel, you will provide commercially focused legal support and advice, and assist management and business units in making sound business decisions. This includes identifying and resolving legal issues or considerations to safeguard operations against any risks whilst building meaningful working relationships with diverse stakeholders including external counsels, and internal and external stakeholders. You will also ensure compliance with local regional regulatory requirements and play an active role in ensuring a strong corporate governance culture.
Job Description:
Guide junior legal counsels in areas of legal advice and contract review;
Provide legal advice to stakeholders and operation teams on a wide range of corporate commercial matters, draft, review, negotiate and advise on agreements related particularly to logistics and supply chain transactions, projects, inter-company matters, leasing, employment, compliance, intellectual property, and other corporate matters;
Risk Management and Problem Solving – Manage the company’s legal risk through anticipating, identifying, and solving legal issues;
Policies & Procedures – Develop and implement legal policies and procedures related to corporate governance, regulatory compliance, and operations;
Project Management – Instruct and work closely with external counsels, draft agreements internally, liaise with both internal stakeholders and external parties to ensure timely desired outcome.
Job Requirements:
A qualified Lawyer with at least 15 to 20 years PQE including experience in litigation, corporate and corporate secretariat work;
Excellent communication, engagement and interpersonal skills to manage multiple levels of the organisation in order to provide legal advice to non-legal stakeholders and operation teams on a wide range of corporate, legal and commercial matters;
Strong analytical skills and proven ability to apply sound, principled and consistent judgement in diverse and challenging legal, business and different cultural environments. Consultative and collaborative in reaching well thought-through solutions;
An ability to balance legal risks and business needs. Comfortable with ambiguity and change, unruffled by uncertainty;
Self-driven, positive and highly adaptable, organised, meticulous and resourceful;
An understanding and experience in the logistics and supply chain and / or healthcare services industry is advantageous;
Proficiency in Microsoft Office is a must.
Are you ready for a challenging and exciting endeavour that will require the investment of a lot of hard work, dedication and all your experience? Are you ready to bring your skills and competencies to support the establishment and enhancement of our client’s business? If yes, you might be exactly the new team member they are looking for!
Please submit your updated and comprehensive CV in MS WORD FORMAT ONLY (NOT PDF) with full career details, stating current or last drawn salary with full breakdown such as base, incentives, AWS, etc. and expected salary, contact details, educational qualifications, working experiences, reasons for leaving each past employment(s) and availability date to:
benchmark.thomas@gmail.com
What our client offers
Our client offers an attractive remuneration package, a fast-paced and exciting working environment and provide challenging opportunities for career advancement. They care about their employees. They are not just an employer. They are a Team. They do not just offer you a job, they offer you a career. By joining their team, you will find strong purpose and deep meaning in everything you do. You will have the chance to make a real difference for customers, working alongside a passionate team of like-minded colleagues, while building your knowledge/skills and developing your career in a fun, dynamic and fast-growing organization.
Personal Data Protection Statement for Job Applicants
Please be informed that the personal data you provided by way of your job application to Benchmark will be collected, used and disclosed by or on behalf of Benchmark to determine or investigate your suitability, eligibility or qualifications for employment with Benchmark and/or its clients and manage your application for employment with Benchmark and/or its clients including identifying you as potential candidate for future suitable positions and/or notifying you of any such positions, either existing or in the future.
Thank You!
We thank all applicants for their interest in a career with our client. Due to the high volume of incoming applications, we will not be able to respond to all applicants. Therefore, only shortlisted applicants will be notified for interviews. All applications will be treated with the strictest confidence.
THOMAS CHAN | MOM CEI No: R1766693 | Benchmark Staffing Solutions | MOM EA Licence: 21C0679 | UEN: 53435609E

Roles & Responsibilities
Job Responsibilities
Draft, review, and negotiate key legal contracts to achieve business objectives, minimize risk and ensure compliance with Company policies, laws, and regulations;
Follow Company legal management principals to establish/carry out local legal management system, including contract/dispute/litigation management, risk and compliance management;
Advise on a wide variety of legal issues, including but not limited to distribution/marketing/product liabilities etc;
Provide litigation assessment counseling and risk mitigation advice to handle disputes and litigation in Singapore;
Act as a business partner to support the achievement of the organization business goals and strategies and , and assist Group legal team to manage legal compliance work ;
Perform other related duties as assigned, based on the business need.

Job Requirements
1-3 years experience in a top tier law firm or multinational company, and recent graduates of top law schools are also considered.
Efficient work habits and be able to identify and resolve problems on a timely basis.
Desire to work independently and cross-functionally in a fast-paced environment.
Excellent oral and written communication skills.

By submitting any application or résumé to us, you will be deemed to have agreed and consented to us disclosing your personal information to prospective employers for their consideration.

We are sorry that only short-listed candidates will be notified.

